{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Charmeleon}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=004|prev=Charmander|nextnum=006|next=Charizard|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Charmeleon}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Charmeleon\n|jname=リザード\n|jtranslit=Rizādo\n|tmname=Lizardo\n|ndex=005\n|oldjdex=230\n|jdex=235\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=084\n|fbrow=141\n|abrow=138\n|obrow=207\n|opbrow=063\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fire\n|category=Flame\n|height-ftin=3\'07"\n|height-m=1.1\n|weight-lbs=41.9\n|weight-kg=19.0\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Blaze\n|abilityd=Solar Power\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Monster\n|egggroup2=Dragon\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evsa=1\n|evsp=1\n|expyield=142\n|oldexp=142\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=31\n|color=Red\n|catchrate=45\n|body=06\n|generation=1\n|pokefordex=charmeleon\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Charmeleon\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'リザード\'\'\' \'\'Lizardo\'\') is a {{type|Fire}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation I]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Charmander}} starting at [[level]] 16 and evolves into {{p|Charizard}} starting at level 36.\n\n==Biology==\nCharmeleon is a bipedal, reptilian Pokémon. It has dark red scales and a cream underside from the chest down. It has narrow, blue eyes and a long snout with a slightly hooked tip. On the back of its head is a single horn-like protrusion. It has relatively long arms with three sharp claws. Its short legs have {{wp|plantigrade}} feet with three claws and cream-colored soles. The tip of its long, powerful tail has a flame burning on it. The temperature rises to unbearable levels if Charmeleon swings its tail.\n\nCharmeleon has a vicious nature and will constantly seek out opponents. Strong opponents excite this Pokémon, causing it to spout bluish-white flames that torch its surroundings. However, it will relax once it has won. It is rare in the wild, but it can be found in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Mountain Pokémon|mountainous areas}}.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Ash Charmeleon M20.png|thumb|250px|left|Charmeleon in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Ash\'s Charmeleon]]=====\n{{Ash}}\'s Charmander evolved into Charmeleon in \'\'[[EP043|March of the Exeggutor Squad]]\'\', which also marked the species\' debut. It quickly grew unruly and [[Obedience|disobedient]]. It evolved into Charizard soon after, in \'\'[[EP046|Attack of the Prehistoric Pokémon]]\'\'.\n\nCharmeleon also appeared in \'\'[[M20|I Choose You!]]\'\', which is set in a different continuity from the main series. In this continuity, it previously belonged to [[Cross]] and evolved from Charmander after defeating a {{p|Jigglypuff}} in {{pkmn|battle}}. It later evolved into Charizard after battling Cross\'s {{p|Lycanroc}}.\n\n=====[[Zippo]]=====\n[[Ritchie]]\'s Charmander, nicknamed [[Zippo]], evolved into a Charmeleon sometime prior to the events of \'\'[[EP221|A Parent Trapped!]]\'\'.\n\n=====[[Alain\'s Charmeleon]]=====\nA Charmeleon appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[XYS02|Mega Evolution Special II]]\'\' as the pre-evolved form of [[Alain]]\'s Charizard.\n\n=====[[Trevor\'s Charmeleon]]=====\n{{an|Trevor}}\'s Charmeleon appeared in \'\'[[XY086|A Legendary Photo Op!]]\'\' after having evolved from a Charmander. It was later revealed to have evolved into Charizard during \'\'[[XY125|A League of His Own!]]\'\'.\n\n=====Other=====\nA Charmeleon appeared in \'\'[[EP087|The Crystal Onix]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Mateo]]. He would commonly use it to make glass. It was also used to battle the titular [[Crystal Onix]], during which it set it alight and defeated it.\n\nA Charmeleon appeared in \'\'[[M04|Celebi: The Voice of the Forest]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Sam]]. It was used to battle the [[Iron-Masked Marauder]]\'s {{p|Sneasel}} and won.\n\nA Charmeleon appeared in \'\'[[AG092|Judgment Day]]\'\', under the ownership of {{OBP|Jimmy|AG092}}. It would help Jimmy with a variety of odd jobs on [[Bomba Island]]. It was later targeted by {{TRT}} in one of their schemes, but it was rescued by Jimmy\'s newly-evolved {{p|Blastoise}}.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA Charmeleon appeared in \'\'[[EP057|The Breeding Center Secret]]\'\' as part of a TV advertisement for [[Cassidy]] and [[Butch]]\'s breeding center, in which it evolved from a Charmander and then into Charizard.\n\nA Charmeleon appeared in \'\'[[PK01|Pikachu\'s Vacation]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon seen at the [[Pokémon Theme Park]].\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Charmeleon appeared in \'\'[[AG191|Once More With Reeling!]]\'\', where it was seen participating in the {{to|Terracotta}} {{pkmn|Contest}}.\n\nA Charmeleon appeared in \'\'[[DP010|Not on MY Watch Ya Don\'t!]]\'\'.\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Kanto}}\n{{Animedexbody|EP043|Charmeleon|Ash\'s Pokédex|Charmeleon, the Flame Pokémon. It has razor-sharp claws and its tail is exceptionally strong.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|original|Kanto}}\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY086|Charmeleon|Serena\'s Pokédex|Charmeleon, the Flame Pokémon and the evolved form of {{p|Charmander}}. Charmeleon knocks down opponents with its tail, then defeats them using razor-sharp claws.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|"XY"|Kalos}}\n\n===In Pokémon Origins===\n[[File:Red Charmeleon PO.png|thumb|left|250px|Charmeleon in [[Pokémon Origins]]]]\n====[[Red\'s Charmeleon]]====\n{{OBP|Red|Origins}}\'s Charmander evolved into a Charmeleon some time after Red beat [[Misty]] but before he faced [[Lt. Surge]] between \'\'[[PO01|File 1: Red]]\'\' and \'\'[[PO02|File 2: Cubone]]\'\'. It later evolved into a Charizard after Red defeated [[Koga]] between \'\'[[PO02|File 2: Cubone]]\'\' and \'\'[[PO03|File 3: Giovanni]]\'\'.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n[[File:X Salame Charmeleon.png|thumb|200px|Charmeleon in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n{{main|Blue\'s Charmeleon}}\n{{main|Salamè}}\nCharmeleon debuted in \'\'[[PS005|Onix is On!]]\'\', where it was seen battling in the [[Pewter Gym]] as one of {{adv|Blue}}\'s Pokémon. He evolved from Charmander sometime between \'\'[[PS003|The Secret of Kangaskhan]]\'\' and this round. When {{adv|Red}} and Blue collided in Celadon City, Red mistakenly picked up the Poké Ball of Blue\'s Charmeleon, but he managed to give it back to Blue later. He has since evolved into {{p|Charizard}} with Blue\'s intense training and became even more powerful, assisting in the defeat of both the [[Team Rocket]] triads [[Koga]] and [[Sabrina]], and continued to act as the powerhouse for both Blue and Red, in the two times it was (temporarily) traded to him since then.\n\nA Charmeleon {{pkmn2|caught}} by {{adv|Crystal}} and lent to {{adv|Emerald}} for his [[Battle Pike]] challenge appeared in \'\'[[PS309|Moving Past Milotic]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Charmeleon were used by {{tc|Galactic Grunt|Team Galactic Grunt}}s in \'\'[[PS424|Exit Empoleon]]\'\' and \'\'[[PS425|Cooling Off Heatran]]\'\'.\n\n{{adv|X}}\'s Charmander, Salamè, evolved into a Charmeleon alongside [[Marisso]], who evolved into a {{p|Quilladin}}, in \'\'[[PAXY22|Quilladin Stands]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Gold & Silver: The Golden Boys manga===\nA Charmeleon appeared in \'\'[[GB04|Let\'s Aim For The Goal!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{tc|Firebreather}} Takeo.\n\n===In the Pokémon Zensho manga===\n{{main|Satoshi\'s Charmeleon (Zensho)}}\nIn [[Pokémon Zensho]], {{Zensho|Satoshi}} has a Charmeleon that evolved from the Charmander he received from [[Professor Oak]]. It later evolves again into Charizard.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Charmeleon (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=fire}}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=I|reg1=Kanto|num1=005}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Red|v2=Blue|t2=FFF|entry=When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Yellow|entry=Tough